author: Associated Press
title: Here's how millions voted in S. Korea amid coronavirus. Could the U.S.?
description: Wednesday's voting draws a contrast with an upended election cycle in the U.S., where some states have pushed back presidential primaries or switched to voting by mail.
content:
SEOUL, South Korea In a surprisingly high turnout, millions of South Korean voters wore masks and moved slowly between lines of tape at polling stations on Wednesday to elect lawmakers in the shadows of the spreading coronavirus.
